time complexity: O(log(right - left))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:
The solution uses a while loop to iterate from left to right, performing a bitwise AND operation on the current number (result) and the current value of left, and then shifting left by one bit. This ensures that the result only considers the least significant bit of the left number at each iteration. The time complexity is O(log(right - left)) due to the iterative approach, and the space complexity is O(1) as we only use a single variable (result) and no additional data structures. The energy implications are low as the solution only performs bitwise operations and does not involve any complex calculations or memory usage.

